New postulates:

1. clopenIsDecidable : (P : hProp) -> isOpenProp P -> isClosedProp P -> Dec P
   If a proposition is both open and closed, it is decidable.
   (ClopenDecidable from tex Corollary 774)
   Proof idea: Uses LLPO on appropriately constructed sequence

2. implicationOpenClosed : (P Q : hProp) -> isOpenProp P -> isClosedProp Q
                         -> isClosedProp (P -> Q)
   If P is open and Q is closed, then P -> Q is closed.
   (ImplicationOpenClosed from tex Lemma 857)
   Proof idea: P -> Q <-> not P \/ Q, and not P is closed (by negOpenIsClosed),
   so by closedOr the result is closed

3. closedMarkov : (P : N -> hProp) -> ((n : N) -> isClosedProp (P n))
                -> not ((n : N) -> not P n) -> || Sigma n. P n ||
   For a sequence of closed propositions, double negation elimination
   for the truncated existential.
   (Related to Lemma 807 from tex)

